information.moreAboutThisHawker: Cheap and homely tasting laksa with a fragrant kick of coconut. Owner is a cool and friendly guy!

location.name: Ghim Moh Market and Hawker Centre

allStalls.name: Ah Liong's Ultimate Kampong Chicken Rice

information.foodTheyServe: Chicken Rice and Curry Chicken Noodles
information.moreAboutThisHawker: Run by bubbly husband wife pair. They just moved down from Serangoon about 4 months ago. Chicken was tender and curry flavour on the mild side. Definitely can eat!

location.name: Ghim Moh Market and Hawker Centre

allStalls.name: An Ji Traditional Hainanese Chicken Rice

information.moreAboutThisHawker: Homely, simple chicken rice that tastes like those I had in primary school. Cooked by a pair of elderly aunties that live nearby. They are also open till quite late.

location.name: Ghim Moh Market and Hawker Centre

information.moreAboutThisHawker: Been eating their duck rice before they were famous and at the old ghim moh market. Queues are insane but the duck rice and noodles are really nice and affordable. Chilli is bombs too. Definitely happy they got a michellin bib gourmand but also means even longer queues :(

location.name: Ghim Moh Market and Hawker Centre

information.moreAboutThisHawker: Butterfly, red bean pastry is really good, especially fresh. Queue is quite long in the mornings.

location.name: Ghim Moh Market and Hawker Centre

information.moreAboutThisHawker: Traditional home-made curry that is thick and tasty. Coconut flavour just right.
information.whatAreTheConcernsThisHawkerIsFacing: Business hit during 2ha, less people dabaoing

information.foodTheyServe: Fish Soup, Vinegar Trotters, Seafood Pao Fan
information.moreAboutThisHawker: Started as a comforting fish soup stall with generous portion but their new additions of seafood pao fan and vinegar trotters are also delicious, which shows the talent of the chef.

location.name: Ghim Moh Market and Hawker Centre

information.moreAboutThisHawker: Took over from the previous prawn noodle recently, run by 2 aunties who know how to make a mean prawn noodle. The soup is super flavourful and the noodles tasty and springy. Small option is also at $3, so many people are lined up for breakfast, lunch and dinner!

location.name: Ghim Moh Market and Hawker Centre

information.favorites: Bitter gourd with egg, Fried Cutlet
information.moreAboutThisHawker: Not your typical Hainan Curry Rice stall, flavours are quite unique and more chinese influenced(?) The family that runs this business are friendly and pleasant to interact with. Sometimes you even get extra at the end of the day. Highly recommend the bitter gourd with egg, stir-fried to perfection

location.name: Ghim Moh Market and Hawker Centre

information.moreAboutThisHawker: Good and cheap cai fan. Very home-cooked style, run by uncle and auntie and their son. Somedays their dishes can be amazing when the chef feels like it. A staple in Ghim Moh market, would recommend it for the unique taste profile

location.name: Ghim Moh Market and Hawker Centre

allStalls.name: Jin Ji Fish Soup Ban Mian

information.moreAboutThisHawker: Relatively new stall but does some delicious ban mian. Soup is super flavourful and free-flow spring onions also helps. The owner is a nice and generous guy and I used to always eat ban mian as a post-workout meal. Highly reccommend the dry you mian with their chilli, does not dissapoint.

location.name: Ghim Moh Market and Hawker Centre

allStalls.name: Rong Xing La Mian Xiao Long Bao

information.moreAboutThisHawker: Decent la mian with chewy texture and guo tie was nice crispy on the outside and juicy on the inside!

allStalls.name: Tong Fong Fatt Hainanese Boneless Chicken Rice

information.favorites: Half a chicken and 2 rice, gizzards!
information.moreAboutThisHawker: Best Chicken Rice in SG. Favourite stall in Ghim Moh ever since childhood. Everyone I have ever brought to try has been a convert. Their chicken is soft, sauce is packed with flavour and the soup is comfort in a bowl. The price has also stayed at $2.50 even after 15 years. If I had 1 stall to recommend in Ghim Moh Market, this would be it. Am good friends with some of the loyal aunties and uncles that have stayed on.

location.name: Ghim Moh Market and Hawker Centre

information.moreAboutThisHawker:
Run by a cute, bubbly elderly couple. Tea is milky and definitely satisftying. Auntie is camera shy but Uncle Mak very cheerful and funny.
They also sell toasts and eggs sets and a kaya drink that looks interesting. Will go back to try!

Always go for their chicken chop and fried chicken wings.Has a very distinctive Singaporean western taste which makes it very familiar to anyone growing up in the early 2000s. The elderly couple running the store are really friendly and nice to talk to. I always ask for extra coleslaw lol

location.name: Ghim Moh Market and Hawker Centre

information.favorites: Fried Mee and Crispy soy skin
information.moreAboutThisHawker: Delicious and homely tasting vegetarian noodles. Auntie can be abit grouchy but once you talk and get to know her she is very nice and will give you more liao
